    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a pretty bold claim about how judges view them. Are you saying the difference in their backgrounds actually makes Case B a higher risk for recidivism, or is it more about how the court perceives their character? Also, can you get more specific on what the actual sentencing recommendation would look like for each—like, would one get probation while the other gets actual jail time?",
